                    <li>
                        <img src="images/apps2019.png" title="" class="img-thumbnail" style="float: right; margin-left: 10px;" />I am happy to announce APPS 2019, the First International Workshop on <a href="http://appsworkshop.cs.ucy.ac.cy/" target="_blank">Adaptive and Personalized Privacy and Security (APPS 2019)</a> which will be collocated with <a href="http://www.cyprusconferences.org/umap2019" target="_blank">ACM UMAP 2019</a>. Submission due date: March 13, 2019</li>
                    <li>The <a href="http://www.cyprusconferences.org/umap2019/pages/cfp.html" target="_blank">Call for Papers of ACM UMAP 2019</a> has been announced. UMAP - User Modelling, Adaptation and Personalization – is the premier international conference for researchers and practitioners working on systems that adapt to individual users, to groups of users, and that collect, represent, and model user information. <small>[Sept. 2018]</small></li>
                    <li>I am happy for <a href="http://www.cs.ucy.ac.cy/~aconst12" target="_blank">Argyris Constantinides</a> first regular paper at <a href="http://www.um.org/umap2018" target="_blank">ACM SIGCHI UMAP 2018</a> related to his Ph.D. work. The paper is entitled <em>"On cultural-centered graphical passwords: Leveraging on users’ cultural experiences for improving password memorability"</em> <small>[April 2018]</small>
                    </li>
                    <li>Full paper accepted at <a href="http://chi2018.acm.org" target="_blank">ACM SIGCHI 2018</a>, entitled <em>"Influences of Human Cognition and Visual Behavior on Password Security during Picture Password Composition"</em> <small>[Dec. 2017]</small></li>
                    <li>Paper accepted for inclusion in the <a href="http://iui.acm.org/2018" target="_blank">ACM SIGCHI IUI 2018</a> Papers' Programme, entitled <em>"Eye Gaze-driven Prediction of Cognitive Differences during Graphical Password Composition"</em> <small>[Dec. 2017]</small></li>
                    <li>New research paper published at ACM Web Intelligence on balancing security and usability in intelligent graphical password schemes (<a href="http://webintelligence2017.com/" target="_blank">ACM WI 2017</a>) <small>[August 2017]</small></li>
                    <li>I am happy for our new research outcomes at Cognitive UX GmbH. Three new research papers; paper on transparently modeling human cognitive styles through eye gaze data (<a href="http://www.um.org/umap2017/" target="_blank">ACM UMAP 2017</a>); paper investigating the interplay among human cognitive factors, technology and user authentication (<a href="https://www.journals.elsevier.com/computers-in-human-behavior" target="_blank">Elsevier CHB</a>); and paper examining the effects of human cognitive strategies on graphical password composition (<a href="https://chi2017.acm.org/" target="_blank">ACM CHI 2017</a>) <small>[May 2017]</small></li>
                    <li>I am co-organizing the workshop on <a href="http://haapie.cs.ucy.ac.cy" target="_blank">Human Aspects in Adaptive and Personalized Interactive Environments (HAAPIE 2016)</a> at <a href="http://www.um.org/umap2016/" target="_blank">ACM UMAP 2016</a>, July 16, 2016, Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada, with <a href="http://scrat.cs.ucy.ac.cy/pgerman/" target="_blank">Panagiotis Germanakos</a>, <a href="http://www.cs.ucy.ac.cy/~cssamara" target="_blank">George Samaras</a> and <a href="http://www.comp.leeds.ac.uk/vania" target="_blank">Vania Dimitrova</a> <small>[July 2016]</small></li>
                    <li>I successfully defended my PhD thesis <a href="http://lekythos.library.ucy.ac.cy/handle/10797/14885" target="_blank">(UCY Library)</a> on December 14, 2015 <small>[December 2015]</small></li>
